item.notes:
Complete line-by-line scansion and discussion, employing the Trager-Smith
               4-level numerical notation. The norm is iambic, with considerable substitu- tion;
               Crannell allows spondees and pyrrhics.

item.bib:
Furnivall, F. J. "The Stopped-Line Test." In New Shakspere Society Prospectus;
                also in The Leopold Shakespeare. London: Cassell, Petter & Galpin, 1873. pp.
                xix- xxii, retitled "Metrical Tests."

Leavis, F. R. "Milton's Verse." Scrutiny 2 (1934): 123-36; rpt in his Revaluation:
                Tradition and Development in English Poetry. London: Chatto & Windus, 1936;
                1953; 1959.

Ramsey, Paul. "The Metrical Rules of the Sonnets." The Fickle Glass: A Study of
                Shakespeare's Sonnets. New York: AMS Press, 1979. pp. 65-98. Summary on pp. 97-98;
                Tables, 209-14.
